├── products.html        # Products listing page
├── favorites.html       # Favorites page
├── cart.html            # Cart and checkout page
├── about.html           # About Us page
├── style.css            # Stylesheet for all pages
├── script.js            # JavaScript file for all pages
└── README.md            # This file

How to Run the Project Locally

Prerequisites
A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, etc.)
A text editor or IDE (e.g., VS Code, Sublime Text) for making any changes
Basic knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Steps to Run
Clone the Repository

Clone the repository to your local machine using the following command:

sh

Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Class-6.git

Or download the ZIP file from the repository and extract it to your preferred location.

Navigate to the Project Directory

Open the terminal (or command prompt) and navigate to the project directory:

sh
Copy code
cd Class-6
Open the index.html File

Use your web browser to open the index.html file. You can do this by right-clicking the file and selecting "Open with" and then choosing your browser, or you can drag and drop the file into your browser window.

